# Styling and Tailwind CSS Patterns

## Tailwind CSS 4.0 Usage
- Use utility-first approach with Tailwind CSS
- Follow the configuration in [components.json](mdc:frontend/components.json)
- Use the "zinc" base color with CSS variables
- Implement consistent spacing and typography scales

## CSS Architecture
- Global styles in [src/styles/globals.css](mdc:frontend/src/styles/globals.css)
- Use CSS variables for theming
- Implement proper CSS custom properties
- Follow BEM-like naming conventions when needed

## Design System
- Follow the established color palette
- Use consistent spacing (4px grid system)
- Implement proper typography scale
- Use consistent border radius and shadows
- Follow accessibility guidelines for contrast

## Responsive Design
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes
- Implement mobile-first design
- Use proper breakpoints for different screen sizes
- Test on various device sizes
- Implement proper touch targets

## Component Styling
- Use Tailwind utilities for component styles
- Implement consistent component variants
- Use CSS-in-JS sparingly and only when necessary
- Follow the established component patterns

## Dark Mode Support
- Implement proper dark mode support
- Use CSS variables for theme switching
- Ensure proper contrast in both themes
- Test accessibility in both modes

## Performance
- Minimize CSS bundle size
- Use Tailwind's purge feature
- Implement proper CSS loading strategies
- Use CSS-in-JS only when necessary
